# Force LF line endings in the repo for all text files. Working trees on
# Windows still see CRLF when they want (git's autocrlf handles that on
# checkout), but the canonical form in git is always LF. Prevents
# spurious "every line changed" diffs when a file round-trips through a
# Windows editor without explicit LF preservation.
#
# This rule only affects the index/commit side — it does NOT renormalize
# files already in the working tree. To clean up existing CRLF files
# later: `git add --renormalize <path>` (do file-by-file to avoid sweeping
# changes into a single commit).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries: explicitly untouched.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.tar binary
*.tar.gz binary
*.gz binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
